21/04/2003
TIRANA, Albania -- Prime Minister Fatos Nano and his Montenegrin counterpart, Milo Djukanovic, signed an agreement Sunday (20 April) on joint efforts against organised crime.
They discussed bilateral ties and opportunities for further co-operation in different areas, including law enforcement.
To that end, they agreed that experts from each country should exchange experiences and enhance co-operation in a bid to prevent trafficking and boost security at borders.
(Shekulli, Koha Jone - 21/04/03;
ATA - 20/04/03)
